parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, wheel lock-up, and accidents.
The failure of the master cylinder can cause brake fluid leakage, extended stopping distances, and accidents.
Worn or warped brake rotors can cause pulsation/vibration, extended stopping distances, and accidents.
The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause brake fluid leakage, extended stopping distances, and accidents.
The failure of the engine mounts can cause engine damage, vibration, and accidents.
The failure of the axle assembly can cause vibration, loss of control, and accidents.
The failure of the transmission cooler hose can cause a fire in the engine compartment, leading to vehicle damage or total loss.
symptoms: smoke or fire from the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause damage to the engine and other components, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: smoke from the bottom of the vehicle
oil leaks from the engine block

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission performance issues can cause poor vehicle performance, leading to accidents or inconvenience.
Vehicle rollaway can cause accidents or injuries, especially if the vehicle is on an incline.
symptoms: Vehicle rolling down a hill after being put in park and key removed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to receive recall notifications or dealers refusing to perform recall repairs can lead to continued vehicle defects and potential safety risks.
symptoms: dealers refusing to perform recall repairs

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or shutting down without warning can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, which can be particularly dangerous for vulnerable individuals such as the elderly or those with disabilities.
Electrical system failures can cause fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
Ignition system failures can cause the vehicle to not start, which can leave the driver stranded, or cause the engine to stall, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: ignition key has to be turned multiple times to start the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is unable to be controlled.
symptoms: unable to disengage by applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery drain can cause the vehicle to not start, which can leave the driver stranded.

Computer problems can cause a range of issues, including engine stalling, electrical system failures, and unintended acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded. Horn issues can cause a lack of warning to other drivers, which can lead to accidents.
